Description: Body sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos or krater; interior smoothed and reserved; exterior,white slip: part of two probably female figures moving left, holding an elaborate wreath between them (of the figure on the left, part of the back, waist with a belt (two incised horizontal lines), buttock, thigh and left arm from below the elbow with the hand holding the wreath; of the right hand figure, only a bit of drapery (added white crosses) and the left hand holding the other side of the wreath); the flesh seems to have been black.
Curator's comments: The smoothness of the interior suggests it is from a dinos or krater.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.9)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1064)
